<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="ToolFaultFinder privacy policy.">
  <div class="wrap page-body">
    <p class="kicker" style="margin-top: 2rem;">The legal bit</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="placeholder-note">
      [PLACEHOLDER - replace with real content] Review and adapt this policy before launch —
      especially if you add analytics, ads, or affiliate links.
    </div>

    <p><em>Last updated: July 2026</em></p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      ToolFaultFinder is a static website. We do not use accounts, tracking cookies, or
      third-party analytics by default. The site's search runs entirely in your browser —
      your search queries never leave your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact form</h2>
    <p>
      If you use the contact form, the details you submit (name, email address, message) are
      processed by Netlify Forms, our hosting provider's form-handling service, and delivered
      to us by email. We use this information only to reply to you. See
      <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" rel="noopener">Netlify's privacy policy</a>
      for how they handle form submissions.
    </p>

    <h2>Server logs</h2>
    <p>
      Our hosting provider (Netlify) may collect standard server logs, including IP addresses,
      for security and operational purposes. We do not access or use these for tracking.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes — for example, if we add analytics — we'll update this page and
      the date above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy? Use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
